# Data Ingestion Rules

## Source Module Structure
Every data source lives in `src/sources/<source-name>/` with this structure:
```
src/sources/gdelt/
├── index.ts          # barrel export
├── fetcher.ts        # raw API call with error handling
├── normalizer.ts     # transforms raw → LebanonEvent[]
├── classifier.ts     # Lumière/Ombre classification logic
├── types.ts          # raw API response types
├── config.ts         # endpoints, TTLs, constants
└── __tests__/
    ├── fetcher.test.ts
    ├── normalizer.test.ts
    └── classifier.test.ts
```

## LebanonEvent Interface (canonical)
All sources MUST normalize to this interface:
```typescript
interface LebanonEvent {
  id: string;                    // unique: `${source}-${sourceId}`
  source: SourceName;            // enum: 'gdelt' | 'usgs' | 'firms' | ...
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  url?: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  latitude: number;
  longitude: number;
  classification: 'lumiere' | 'ombre' | 'neutre';
  confidence: number;            // 0-1
  category: EventCategory;       // enum defined in types
  severity: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'critical';
  rawData?: Record<string, unknown>;
  metadata: {
    fetchedAt: Date;
    ttlSeconds: number;
    sourceReliability: 'high' | 'medium' | 'low';
  };
}
```

## Fetcher Rules
- Every fetcher MUST have a configurable timeout (default 10s)
- Every fetcher MUST use AbortController for cancellation
- Every fetcher MUST return `Result<T, SourceError>` pattern
- Every fetcher MUST log: source name, response time, status code, event count
- Rate limiting: respect source TTLs, never poll faster than config
- Retry: max 2 retries with exponential backoff for 5xx errors
- Never retry on 4xx errors (bad request = our bug)

## Classifier Rules
- Lumière/Ombre classification uses keyword dictionaries + tone scores
- Keyword dictionaries are in `src/lib/classification/dictionaries/`
- Three language dictionaries: Arabic, French, English
- GDELT tone score mapping: tone > 3 → lumière, tone < -3 → ombre, else neutre
- CAMEO Goldstein scale: > 5 → lumière, < -5 → ombre
- Always output a confidence score between 0 and 1
- Log classification decisions for review

## API Route Rules
- All API routes go in `src/app/api/sources/[source]/route.ts`
- Use NextResponse with proper status codes
- Add Cache-Control headers matching source TTL
- Validate query params with Zod schemas
- Return typed JSON responses

## Testing Requirements
- Every source MUST have fixture files in `__tests__/fixtures/`
- Fixtures are real API responses saved as JSON
- Tests MUST work offline (no live API calls in tests)
- Test: fetcher error handling, normalizer output shape, classifier accuracy
- Minimum: 3 test cases per source (happy path, error, edge case)

## Priority Sources (Phase 1)
Implement in this exact order:
1. GDELT DOC API (events + tone)
2. USGS Earthquake API (seismic)
3. NASA FIRMS (fires)
4. RSS feeds (6-8 Lebanese media)
5. GDACS (disasters)
6. ReliefWeb API (humanitarian)
7. OpenWeatherMap (weather)
8. Cloudflare Radar (internet outages)
9. LBP/USD scraper (exchange rate)
10. OpenAQ (air quality)
